cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of generating 3D mesh representations from 2D images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The use of a graph convolutional network also suggests a potential connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions physically driven architecture, which could relate to multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
